                                <locus from="1r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayers</title>
                                <rubric>orationes ad sepulcrum domini hec<sic> dicuntu</sic>
                                </rubric>
                                <incipit>PEr gloriam sanctissime resurectionis tue </incipit>
                                <explicit defective="unknown">integritatem mentis tutelam salutis securitatem spei coroboracionem fidei hic et in eterna secula seculorum amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2va" to="5rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Names of the months written both in Latin and Czech.</p>
                                    <p> Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3ra" to="3ra" scheme="folios"/> Sts Cyril and Methodius (9 Mar.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3va" to="3va" scheme="folios"/> St Sigismund (2 May);</p>
                                    <p> St Stanislaus (8 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3vb" to="3vb" scheme="folios"/> St Vitus (15 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4ra" to="4ra" scheme="folios"/> St Procopius (4 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4va" to="4va" scheme="folios"/> St Ludmilla (16 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p> St Wenceslaus (28 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4vb" to="4vb" scheme="folios"/> St Cordula (22 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5ra" to="5ra" scheme="folios"/> Translation of St Ludmilla (10 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p> Quinque fratrum (12 Nov.).</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="5va" to="5vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Formulary</title>
                                <incipit>Notandum quod oraciones que ad precem sine alterius persone <del>dirig</del> expressione diriguntur sic concluduntur</incipit>
                                <explicit>Eiusdem dicas domini spiritus intus habetur</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="6ra" to="111va" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <rubric>dominica prima in aduentu domini</rubric>
                                <incipit>officians indutus nigra cappa incipit ad aspersionem <gap reason="editorial"/> Ad te leuaui animam meam deus meus (Ps. 24:1)</incipit>
                                <explicit>et corporis tui temporalis percepcio presignat Qui uiuis feria sexta et sabbato ad missam omnia ut ?Gen/hen? recitata sunt <gap reason="editorial"/> per totum ut habetur immediate post Canonem </explicit>
                                <note>The Proper of time begins with the First Sunday of Advent and the first part ends with the First sunday after Trinity. The proper of time is continued after the Ordo and Canon missae.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="111va" to="121va" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ordo and Canon missae</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit accessus altaris quando se presbiter preparat ad missam et primo hos psalmos dicat</rubric>
                                <incipit>psalmus Quam dilecta tabernacula (Ps 83:2)</incipit>
                                <explicit>Dominus ihesus christus det nobis suam pacem Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="117r" to="117r" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="118ra" to="118ra" scheme="folios"/>: Canon.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="121va" to="161ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time (continued)</title>
                                <rubric>Sequitur dominicale officium </rubric>
                                <incipit>Domine in tua misericordia speraui</incipit>
                                <explicit>omnibus dico vigilate nota quia quibusdam annis solet <gap reason="editorial"/> adequalem concordiam reducantur </explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The proper of time continues with the First sunday after Trinity and ends with the Twenty-fifth Sunday after Trinity and a list of exemptions.</p>
                                    <p>The foliator has skipped from f. 138 to f. 140, omitting f. 139, there is no gap in the text.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="161ra" to="162a" scheme="other"/>
                                <title type="desc">Dedication of the church </title>
                                <rubric>Sequitur in dedicacione ecclesie ad missam introitus </rubric>
                                <incipit>Terribilis est locus iste</incipit>
                                <explicit>te ducente peruenire mereamur Per dominum</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
